'''Alejandro''' "'''Álex'''" '''Grimaldo García''' (born 20 September 1995) is a Spanish professional [[Association football|footballer]] who plays as a [[left wing-back]] for {{German football updater|BaLeverk}} club [[Bayer 04 Leverkusen|Bayer Leverkusen]] and the [[Spain national football team|Spain national team]].

==Club career==
===Barcelona===
[[File:Álex Grimaldo.jpg|thumb|left|200px|Grimaldo with [[FC Barcelona|Barcelona]] in 2012]]
Born in [[Valencia]], [[Valencian Community]], Grimaldo joined [[FC Barcelona|Barcelona]]'s youth system in 2008. He made his official debut for [[FC Barcelona B|the B-team]] on 4 September 2011, starting in a 4–0 away win against [[FC Cartagena|Cartagena]] at the age of 15 years and 349 days and becoming the youngest player ever to appear in a [[Segunda División]] game, before he was surpassed by [[Lamine Yamal]] in 2023.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.marca.com/2011/09/04/futbol/2adivision/1315159792.html|title=Vuelve el mejor Barça B con un festival goleador en Cartagonova|trans-title=The best Barça B return with a scoring festival in Cartagonova|newspaper=[[Marca (newspaper)|Marca]]|last=García|first=Gregorio|language=Spanish|date=4 September 2011|access-date=6 September 2011|archive-date=24 July 2015|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150724163700/http://www.marca.com/2011/09/04/futbol/2adivision/1315159792.html|url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.mundodeportivo.com/20110905/fc-barcelona/grimaldo-la-seduccion-de-un-lateral-de-15-anos_54212116164.html|title=Alejandro Grimaldo, la seducción de un lateral de 15 años|trans-title=Alejandro Grimaldo, the allure of a 15-year-old fullback|newspaper=[[Mundo Deportivo]]|last=Gascón|first=Javier|language=Spanish|date=5 September 2011|access-date=12 December 2018|archive-date=7 April 2023|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230407081939/https://www.mundodeportivo.com/20110905/fc-barcelona/grimaldo-la-seduccion-de-un-lateral-de-15-anos_54212116164.html|url-status=live}}</ref>

On 23 February 2013, Grimaldo suffered a serious knee injury, being ruled out for the remainder of [[2012–13 Segunda División|the season]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.fcbarcelona.es/futbol/barca-b/detalle/noticia/alejandro-grimaldo-sufre-una-rotura-del-ligamento-cruzado-anterior-y-del-ligamento-lateral-externo-de-la-rodilla|title=Alejandro Grimaldo sufre una rotura del ligamento cruzado anterior y del ligamento lateral externo de la rodilla|trans-title=Alejandro Grimaldo suffers an anterior cruciate ligament and a lateral collateral injury|publisher=FC Barcelona|language=Spanish|date=24 February 2013|access-date=22 September 2014|archive-date=24 September 2015|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150924030359/http://www.fcbarcelona.es/futbol/barca-b/detalle/noticia/alejandro-grimaldo-sufre-una-rotura-del-ligamento-cruzado-anterior-y-del-ligamento-lateral-externo-de-la-rodilla|url-status=live}}</ref> He returned to action in January of the following year,<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.sport.es/es/noticias/liga-adelante/grimaldo-vuelve-ante-mirandes-masip-queda-fuera-3022290|title=Grimaldo vuelve ante el Mirandés... y Masip se queda fuera|trans-title=Grimaldo returns against Mirandés... and Masip stays out|newspaper=[[Sport (Spanish newspaper)|Sport]]|language=es|date=18 January 2014|access-date=22 September 2014|archive-date=24 September 2015|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150924134828/http://www.sport.es/es/noticias/liga-adelante/grimaldo-vuelve-ante-mirandes-masip-queda-fuera-3022290|url-status=live}}</ref> appearing in 14 matches to help his team finish in third position.

On 13 September 2014, Grimaldo scored his first professional goal, netting his side's last in a 3–2 success at [[Deportivo Alavés|Alavés]].<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.marca.com/2014/09/13/futbol/2adivision/1410636355.html|title=El Barça B se lleva los tres puntos con susto final|trans-title=Barça B take the three points with a final scare|newspaper=Marca|language=es|date=13 September 2014|access-date=22 September 2014|archive-date=16 June 2015|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150616092705/http://www.marca.com/2014/09/13/futbol/2adivision/1410636355.html|url-status=live}}</ref> In [[2014–15 Segunda División|a campaign which saw the team relegated]], he netted four times in 36 matches; he and [[Sergi Palencia]] were [[Ejection (sports)|sent off]] on 25 April 2015, in a 2–1 win over [[SD Ponferradina|Ponferradina]] at the [[Mini Estadi]].<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.marca.com/2015/04/25/futbol/2adivision/1429992631.html|title=Una genialidad de Munir da aire a un filial que acabó con nueve|trans-title=Genius from Munir gives air to a reserve team which finished with nine|newspaper=Marca|language=es|date=25 April 2015|access-date=20 October 2015|archive-date=7 April 2023|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230407081951/https://www.marca.com/2015/04/25/futbol/2adivision/1429992631.html|url-status=live}}</ref>

===Benfica===
On 29 December 2015, as his contract was about to expire,<ref>{{cite news|first=Carlos|last=Nogueira|title=Grimaldo ruma à Luz por um milhão de euros|trans-title=Grimaldo heads to Luz for one million euros|url=https://www.dn.pt/desporto/benfica/interior/grimaldo-ruma-a-luz-por-um-milhao-de-euros-4944617.html|newspaper=[[Diário de Notícias]]|date=18 December 2015|access-date=27 December 2015|language=pt|archive-date=2 April 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190402155313/https://www.dn.pt/desporto/benfica/interior/grimaldo-ruma-a-luz-por-um-milhao-de-euros-4944617.html|url-status=live}}</ref> Grimaldo signed with Portuguese champions [[S.L. Benfica|Benfica]] until 2021, for €1.5 million. Barcelona has the right to a percentage of a future sale.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.slbenfica.pt/noticias/detalhedenoticia/tabid/2788/ArticleId/44196/language/pt-PT/.aspx|title="Tenho muita ambição em crescer neste clube"|trans-title=I have a lot of ambition of growing in this club|publisher=S.L. Benfica|language=pt|date=29 December 2015|access-date=29 December 2015|archive-date=1 January 2016|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160101121420/http://www.slbenfica.pt/noticias/detalhedenoticia/tabid/2788/ArticleId/44196/language/pt-PT/.aspx|url-status=live}}</ref>

Grimaldo played his first game with his new team on 26 January 2016, coming in as a 62nd-minute [[Substitute (association football)|substitute]] for [[Sílvio Manuel Pereira|Sílvio]] in a 6–1 away routing of [[Moreirense F.C.|Moreirense]] for the [[Taça da Liga]].<ref>{{cite web|title=Classe e magia no check-in para as "meias"|trans-title=Class and magic in "semis" check-in|url=http://www.slbenfica.pt/noticias/detalhedenoticia/tabid/2788/ArticleId/44510/language/pt-PT/Classe-e-magia-no-check-in-para-as-meias.aspx|website=Benfica|date=26 January 2016|access-date=27 January 2016|language=pt|archive-date=14 April 2016|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160414214846/http://www.slbenfica.pt/noticias/detalhedenoticia/tabid/2788/ArticleId/44510/language/pt-PT/Classe-e-magia-no-check-in-para-as-meias.aspx|url-status=live}}</ref> He debuted in the [[Primeira Liga]] on 29 February, featuring the full 90 minutes in a 2–0 home win against [[C.F. União|União da Madeira]];<ref>{{cite web|title=Quem tem um Jonas, tem tudo|trans-title=He who has a Jonas, has everything|url=https://rr.sapo.pt/noticia/48101/quem_tem_um_jonas_tem_tudo|publisher=[[Rádio Renascença]]|date=29 February 2016|access-date=1 March 2016|language=pt|archive-date=5 April 2023|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230405195747/https://rr.sapo.pt/noticia/48101/quem_tem_um_jonas_tem_tudo|url-status=live}}</ref> he only appeared once more in the latter competition until the end of [[2015–16 Primeira Liga|the season]], filling in for suspended [[Eliseu]]<ref>{{cite news|url=http://comunidade.jn.pt/PaginaInicial/Desporto/Interior.aspx?content_id=5175319|title=Gaitán volta com Talisca e Grimaldo no onze|trans-title=Gaitán returns with Talisca and Grimaldo in XI|newspaper=[[Jornal de Notícias]]|date=14 May 2016|access-date=16 May 2016|language=pt|archive-date=20 December 2016|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20161220072728/http://comunidade.jn.pt/PaginaInicial/Desporto/Interior.aspx?content_id=5175319|url-status=dead}}</ref> in a 4–1 victory over [[C.D. Nacional|Nacional]] also at the [[Estádio da Luz]] that sealed the club's third consecutive national championship.<ref name=TRI>{{cite web|url=https://desporto.sapo.pt/futebol/primeira_liga/artigo/2016/05/15/benfica-tricampeao-nacional-de-futebol|title=Génio de Gaitán dá o 'tri' ao Benfica|trans-title=Gaitán genius gives "tri" to Benfica|website=SAPO|date=15 May 2016|access-date=16 May 2016|publisher=pt|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20161220074418/http://desporto.sapo.pt/futebol/primeira_liga/artigo/2016/05/15/benfica-tricampeao-nacional-de-futebol|archive-date=20 December 2016 |url-status=live}}</ref> He remained in the team for the [[2016 Taça da Liga Final|league cup final]] on 20 May, the 6–2 defeat of [[C.S. Marítimo|Marítimo]] at the [[Estádio Cidade de Coimbra]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://desporto.sapo.pt/futebol/taca_da_liga/artigo/2016/05/20/cronica-final-final-taca-da-liga-2016|title=Benfica continua a ser o rei da Taça da Liga|trans-title=Benfica are still League Cup kings|publisher=SAPO|date=20 May 2016|access-date=24 March 2017|language=pt|archive-date=23 May 2016|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160523104551/http://desporto.sapo.pt/futebol/taca_da_liga/artigo/2016/05/20/cronica-final-final-taca-da-liga-2016|url-status=live}}</ref>

[[File:Grimaldo Benfica-Zenit UCL201920.jpg|thumb|upright=0.6|Grimaldo with Benfica in 2019]]
Grimaldo's [[2016–17 Primeira Liga|first full season]] began on 7 August 2016, as he started in a 3–0 win against [[S.C. Braga|Braga]] for the [[Supertaça Cândido de Oliveira]] in [[Aveiro, Portugal|Aveiro]], assisting [[Franco Cervi]] for the opening goal.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://futbol.as.com/futbol/2016/08/08/internacional/1470607422_553441.html|title=El Benfica campeón de la Supercopa gracias a Cervi y Pizzi|trans-title=Benfica are Supercup champions thanks to Cervi and Pizzi|newspaper=[[Diario AS]]|date=8 August 2016|language=es|access-date=24 March 2017|archive-date=17 May 2017|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170517002608/http://futbol.as.com/futbol/2016/08/08/internacional/1470607422_553441.html|url-status=live}}</ref> On 2 October he scored his first goal for the club, a [[Direct free kick|free kick]] to conclude a 4–0 home triumph over [[C.D. Feirense|Feirense]];<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.cmjornal.pt/desporto/futebol/detalhe/benfica-0-0-feirense-siga-em-direto|title=Benfica goleia o Feirense|trans-title=Benfica thrash Feirense|newspaper=[[Correio da Manhã (Portugal)|Correio da Manhã]]|language=pt|date=2 October 2016|access-date=24 March 2017|archive-date=7 April 2023|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230407081951/https://www.cmjornal.pt/desporto/futebol/detalhe/benfica-0-0-feirense-siga-em-direto|url-status=live}}</ref> on 28 May 2017, he played the full 90 minutes in [[2017 Taça de Portugal Final|the final]] of the [[Taça de Portugal]], won after defeating [[Vitória S.C.|Vitória de Guimarães]] 2–1.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.dn.pt/desporto/benfica/interior/entre-a-11a-dobradinha-do-benfica-e-a-segunda-taca-do-vitoria-8513638.html|title=Oito minutos à Benfica garantiram a 11.ª dobradinha|trans-title=Eight Benfica-like minutes confirmed 11th double|newspaper=Diário de Notícias|date=28 May 2017|access-date=13 May 2018|language=pt|archive-date=12 June 2018|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180612184600/https://www.dn.pt/desporto/benfica/interior/entre-a-11a-dobradinha-do-benfica-e-a-segunda-taca-do-vitoria-8513638.html|url-status=live}}</ref>

Grimaldo's maiden appearance in the [[UEFA Champions League]] took place on 13 September 2016, when he played the entire 1–1 group stage home draw to [[Beşiktaş J.K.|Beşiktaş]].<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.dn.pt/desporto/benfica/interior/ederson-na-baliza-cervi-e-goncalo-guedes-no-ataque-ao-besiktas-5387639.html|title=Talisca, o dispensado, roubou uma vitória que parecia certa|trans-title=Talisca, the surplus, robbed almost certain win|newspaper=Diário de Notícias|date=13 September 2016|access-date=12 December 2018|language=pt|archive-date=2 April 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190402155043/https://www.dn.pt/desporto/benfica/interior/ederson-na-baliza-cervi-e-goncalo-guedes-no-ataque-ao-besiktas-5387639.html|url-status=live}}</ref> His first goal in the competition came during the same stage but on 2 October 2018, in a 3–2 away win over [[AEK Athens F.C.|AEK Athens]];<ref>{{cite news|first=Mariana|last=Béu|title=Benfica com triunfo sofrido sobre o AEK (3–2). Seferovic e Grimaldo marcaram, gregos empataram e Alfa Semedo resolveu – como aconteceu|trans-title=Benfica with hard-fought win over AEK (3–2). Seferovic and Grimaldo scored, Greek drew and Alfa Semedo decided it – how it happened|url=https://observador.pt/2018/10/02/benfica-na-grecia-a-procura-de-somar-os-primeiros-pontos-no-grupo-e-da-champions-frente-ao-aek-20-horas-siga-em-direto/|newspaper=Observador|date=2 October 2018|access-date=13 December 2018|language=pt}}</ref> he repeated the feat against the latter opponent on 12 December in the return fixture, his 30-meter [[Direct free kick|free-kick]] in the 88th minute helping to a 1–0 victory.<ref>{{cite web|first=Marcos|last=Celso|title=Benfica vence AEK de Atenas com grande golo de Grimaldo|trans-title=Benfica beat AEK Athens with great Grimaldo goal|url=https://www.rtp.pt/noticias/futebol-internacional/benfica-vence-aek-de-atenas-com-grande-golo-de-grimaldo_d1116971|website=[[Rádio e Televisão de Portugal]]|date=12 December 2018|access-date=12 December 2018|archive-date=7 April 2023|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230407011030/https://www.rtp.pt/noticias/futebol-internacional/benfica-vence-aek-de-atenas-com-grande-golo-de-grimaldo_d1116971|url-status=live}}</ref>

===Bayer Leverkusen===
On 21 May 2023, Grimaldo signed a four-year contract with German club [[Bayer 04 Leverkusen|Bayer Leverkusen]] on a [[Free transfer (association football)|free transfer]].<ref>{{Cite web |date=21 May 2023 |title=Bayer 04 sign Grimaldo from Benfica |url=https://www.bayer04.de/en-us/news/bayer04/%7B%7B%20vm.common.getSiteCanonicalTag()%20%7C%20trustUrl%20%7D%7D |access-date=3 July 2023 |website=BAYER 04 LEVERKUSEN |archive-date=24 July 2023 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230724110955/https://www.bayer04.de/en-us/news/bayer04/%7B%7B%20vm.common.getSiteCanonicalTag%28%29%20%7C%20trustUrl%20%7D%7D |url-status=live }}</ref> On 12 August, he debuted in a [[2023–24 DFB-Pokal|DFB-Pokal]] match against [[FC Teutonia Ottensen]].<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.sportschau.de/fussball/dfbpokal/spielbericht-teutonia-bayer-leverkusen-dfb-pokal-100.html |title=Leverkusen bezwingt Ottensen klar und deutlich |publisher=sportschau.de |language=de |date=12 August 2023 |access-date=15 September 2023 |archive-date=8 September 2023 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230908175229/https://www.sportschau.de/fussball/dfbpokal/spielbericht-teutonia-bayer-leverkusen-dfb-pokal-100.html |url-status=live }}</ref> On 15 September, he scored his first goal for the club, a direct free kick from the edge of the box away at [[FC Bayern Munich|Bayern Munich]] in a 2–2 draw.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.bundesliga.com/en/news/Bundesliga/xabi-alonso-s-bayer-leverkusen-grateful-for-alex-grimaldo-s-on-field-mastery-24996 |title=FC Bayern München 2–2 Bayer 04 Leverkusen |publisher=Bundesliga |date=15 September 2023 |access-date=4 November 2023 |archive-date=4 November 2023 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20231104173556/https://www.bundesliga.com/en/bundesliga/news/xabi-alonso-s-bayer-leverkusen-grateful-for-alex-grimaldo-s-on-field-mastery-24996 |url-status=live }}</ref> On 14 April 2024, Leverkusen beat [[SV Werder Bremen|Werder Bremen]] 5-0 to secure the first Bundesliga title in the club's history. Grimaldo assisted the fifth goal of the game.<ref>{{Cite web |title=Bayer Leverkusen beat Bremen to win the Bundesliga! |url=https://www.bundesliga.com/en/bundesliga/news/bayer-leverkusen-werder-bremen-xabi-alonso-champions-title-free-highlights-26914 |access-date=30 October 2025 |website=www.bundesliga.com |language=en}}</ref>

Grimaldo was named in the [[2023–24 Bundesliga]]'s team of the season, finishing as the top assist provider in the Bundesliga with 13 assists and being involved in more goals than any other Leverkusen player despite playing as a left-back.<ref>{{cite web |title=Bundesliga Stats 2023-2024 |url=https://www.bundesliga.com/en/bundesliga/stats/players/assists/2023-2024 |access-date=23 May 2024 |publisher=Bundesliga}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |title=Confirmed: Bundesliga Team of the Season 2023/24 by EA FC 24! |url=https://www.bundesliga.com/en/bundesliga/news/vote-now-for-the-bundesliga-team-of-the-season-2023-24-with-ea-fc-24-26961 |access-date=30 October 2025 |website=www.bundesliga.com |language=en}}</ref> Grimaldo was later nominated for the [[2024 Ballon d'Or]] for his performances in Leverkusen's unbeaten [[Double (association football)|league and cup double]].<ref>{{Cite web |title=Bayern Munich's Harry Kane and Bayer Leverkusen trio among Bundesliga nominees for Ballon d'Or |url=https://www.bundesliga.com/en/bundesliga/news/harry-kane-florian-wirtz-ballon-dor-nominees-xhaka-grimaldo-28794 |access-date=30 October 2025|website=www.bundesliga.com |language=en}}</ref>

On 13 September 2025, Grimaldo scored two free-kicks in a 3-1 win over [[Eintracht Frankfurt]], in [[Kasper Hjulmand]]'s first match as Leverkusen coach. This was the first time in over a decade that a player had scored two free-kicks in one Bundesliga game.<ref>{{Cite web |title=Bayer Leverkusen's 'free-kick monster' Alejandro Grimaldo a nightmare for Bundesliga goalkeepers |url=https://www.bundesliga.com/en/bundesliga/news/bayer-leverkusen-alejandro-grimaldo-set-piece-king-eintracht-frankfurt-34037 |access-date=30 October 2025|website=www.bundesliga.com |language=en}}</ref> On 18 October, Grimaldo scored another brace, in a 4-3 win over [[1. FSV Mainz 05|Mainz]]. He was nominated for the Bundesliga Player of The Month award for October.<ref>{{Cite web |title=Alejandro Grimaldo's double helps Bayer Leverkusen edge seven-goal thriller against Mainz |url=https://www.bundesliga.com/en/bundesliga/news/mainz-bayer-leverkusen-match-report-highlights-matchday-7-grimaldo-34449 |access-date=30 October 2025|website=www.bundesliga.com |language=en}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |title=Who will be your Bundesliga Player of the Month for October? |url=https://www.bundesliga.com/en/bundesliga/news/player-of-the-month-2025-26-vote-winners-ea-sports-34233 |access-date=30 October 2025 |website=www.bundesliga.com |language=en}}</ref>

==International career==
Grimaldo won his first [[Cap (sport)|call-up]] for the [[Spain national under-21 football team|Spain under-21 team]] on 5 February 2013 before he had turned 18, playing the second half of a 1–1 [[Exhibition game#Association football|friendly]] draw in [[Belgium national under-21 football team|Belgium]].<ref>{{cite news|first=Fran|last=Villalobos|title=España invierte en su futuro|trans-title=Spain invest in their future|url=http://www.marca.com/2013/02/05/futbol/cantera/1360098317.html|website=Marca|date=5 February 2013|access-date=27 December 2015|language=es|archive-date=5 January 2016|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160105103950/http://www.marca.com/2013/02/05/futbol/cantera/1360098317.html|url-status=live}}</ref>

On 10 November 2023, Grimaldo received his first call-up to the [[Spain national football team|Spain senior national team]], for [[UEFA Euro 2024 qualifying Group A|Euro 2024 qualifiers]] against [[Cyprus national football team|Cyprus]] and [[Georgia national football team|Georgia]].<ref>{{Cite web |last= |date=10 November 2023 |title=Grimaldo convocado pela primeira vez para a seleção espanhola |trans-title=Grimaldo called-up for the first time for the Spanish national team |url=https://www.abola.pt/futebol/noticias/grimaldo-convocado-pela-primeira-vez-para-a-selecao-espanhola-2023111010370900231 |access-date=10 November 2023 |website= |publisher=A Bola |language=pt|archive-date=10 November 2023 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20231110131418/https://www.abola.pt/futebol/noticias/grimaldo-convocado-pela-primeira-vez-para-a-selecao-espanhola-2023111010370900231 |url-status=live }}</ref> Six days later, he made his debut as a starter against Cyprus, assisting [[Mikel Oyarzabal]] for Spain's second goal in a 3–1 away victory.<ref>{{Cite web |last= |date=16 November 2023 |title=Euro-2024 Espanha derrota Chipre com boa estreia de Grimaldo |trans-title=Euro 2024 Spain beats Cyprus with good debut by Grimaldo |url=https://www.abola.pt/futebol/noticias/espanha-derrota-chipre-com-boa-estreia-de-grimaldo-2023111619171654532 |access-date=16 November 2023 |website= |publisher=A Bola |language=pt|archive-date=16 November 2023 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20231116220724/https://www.abola.pt/futebol/noticias/espanha-derrota-chipre-com-boa-estreia-de-grimaldo-2023111619171654532 |url-status=live }}</ref>

In May 2024, he was named in Spain's 26-man squad for the [[UEFA Euro 2024]].<ref>{{Cite web |last=UEFA.com |title=Spain {{!}} Squad |url=https://www.uefa.com/euro2024/teams/122--spain/squad/ |access-date=15 July 2024 |website=[[UEFA]] |language=en}}</ref> Grimaldo was widely expected to be a starter, but [[Marc Cucurella]] was ultimately preferred, though Grimaldo did play in the 1-0 win over [[Albania national football team|Albania]] and the 4-1 win over [[Georgia national football team|Georgia]].<ref>{{Cite news |last=Lowe |first=Sid |date=11 October 2024 |title=Marc Cucurella: ‘Before, people liked the superstars, now they empathise with me’ |url=https://www.theguardian.com/football/2024/oct/11/marc-cucurella-spain-chelsea-euro-2024-interview |access-date=30 October 2024 |work=The Guardian |language=en-GB |issn=0261-3077}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |date=16 July 2024 |title=Chelsea news: Learnings from Marc Cucurella's Euro 2024 |url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/articles/c2q01zxw445o |access-date=30 October 2024 |website=BBC Sport |language=en-GB}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |last=UEFA.com |title=History: Spain 4-1 Georgia {{!}} UEFA EURO 2024 |url=https://www.uefa.com/uefaeuro/match/2036199--spain-vs-georgia/ |access-date=30 October 2025 |website=UEFA.com |language=en}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |last=UEFA.com |title=History: Albania 0-1 Spain {{!}} UEFA EURO 2024 |url=https://www.uefa.com/uefaeuro/match/2036187--albania-vs-spain/ |access-date=30 October 2025 |website=UEFA.com |language=en}}</ref>

